00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:26,717
<i>Mutation: it is the key to our evolution.</i>

2
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:32,358
<i>lt has enabled us to evolve</i>
<i>into the dominant species on the planet.</i>

3
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:36,837
<i>This process normally takes</i>
<i>thousands and thousands of years.</i>

4
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:41,192
<i>But every few hundred millennia,</i>
<i>evolution leaps forward.</i>

5
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,511
Niagara Falls,

6
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,790
up the Canadian Rockies,

7
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:23,708
and then it's only
a few hundred miles to Anchorage.

8
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:27,515
- Won't it kinda be cold?
- Well, that's the point, stupid.

9
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:30,552
Otherwise it wouldn't be an adventure.

10
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:33,353
And when are you gonna do this?

11
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:37,993
l don't know.

12
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:41,351
After high school. Before college.

13
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,830
- Marie!
- l don't know what happened.

14
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:29,714
- David?
- l don't know... l just touched him.

15
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:32,673
- l didn't mean...
- Call an ambulance!

16
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,598
We only touched. Just get away from me!

17
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:38,996
- Will you call an ambulance?!
- Don't touch me!

18
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:45,717
We are now seeing the beginnings
of another stage of human evolution.

19
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:51,153
These mutations manifest at puberty, often
triggered by periods of emotional stress.

20
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:54,431
Thank you, Miss Grey.
lt was quite educational.

21
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:58,712
However, it fails to address the issue
that is the focus of this hearing.

22
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:02,435
Three words: are mutants dangerous?

23
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:08,078
That's unfair, Senator Kelly. The wrong
person driving a car can be dangerous.

24
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:11,749
- We do license people to drive.
- Yes, but not to live.

25
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:17,355
Senator, mutants who've come forward
and revealed themselves publicly

26
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:20,916
have been met with fear,
hostility, even violence.

27
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,395
lt is because of that hostility

28
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:27,559
that l am urging the Senate
to vote against mutant registration.

29
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:30,911
- To force mutants to expose themselves...
- Expose themselves?

30
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:35,556
What do mutants have to hide that makes
them so afraid to identify themselves?

31
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:39,719
- l didn't say they were hiding.
- Let me show you what is being hidden.

32
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:45,358
l have here a list of names of identified
mutants living right here in the United States.

33
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:49,109
- Senator Kelly...
- A girl in lllinois who walks through walls.

34
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:53,631
What's to stop her from walking
into a bank vault? Or into the White House?

35
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:58,914
Or into <i>their</i> houses? And there are even
rumours of mutants so powerful

36
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:02,077
that they can enter our minds
and control our thoughts,

37
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,555
taking away our God-given free will.

38
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:09,196
The American people deserve the right
to decide whether they want their children

39
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:13,154
to be in school with mutants.
To be taught by mutants.

40
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:20,000
Ladies and gentlemen,
the truth is that mutants are very real.

41
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:25,512
And they are among us.
We must know who they are,

42
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:29,519
and, above all,
we must know what they can do.

43
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:54,316
Eric.

44
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,556
What are you doing here?

45
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:02,753
Why do you ask questions to which
you already know the answers?

46
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:07,032
- Don't give up on them, Eric.
- What would you have me do, Charles?

47
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:10,436
l've heard these arguments before.

48
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:14,599
lt was a long time ago.
Mankind has evolved since then.

49
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:18,157
Yes... into us.

50
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:29,672
Are you sneaking around in here, Charles?
Whatever are you looking for?

51
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,711
l'm looking for hope.

52
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:44,830
l will bring you hope, old friend.
And l ask only one thing in return.

53
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,115
Don't get in my way.

54
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:56,753
We are the future, Charles, not them!
They no longer matter.

55
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:12,276
This is it.

56
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:24,117
Where are we? l thought you said you were
gonna take me as far as Laughlin City.

57
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,196
This <i>is</i> Laughlin City.

58
00:09:56,480 --> 00:10:01,031
Gentlemen, in all my years
l've never seen anything like this.

59
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:06,912
Are you gonna let this man
walk away with your money?

60
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,314
No!

61
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:11,159
l'll fight him!

62
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:15,400
Ladies and gentlemen,

63
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:17,476
our saviour!

64
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,950
Don't hit him in the balls.

65
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:25,312
- You said anything goes.
- Anything goes, but he'll take it personal.

66
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:38,478
You idiot!

67
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:56,437
Ladies and gentlemen,
tonight's winner and still King of the Cage,

68
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:58,790
the Wolverine.

69
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:31,310
You want something new, honey?
Or are you sticking with water?

70
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,916
l'll have a beer.

71
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:55,119
<i>Ellis lsland, once the arrival point</i>
<i>for American immigrants,</i>

72
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,276
<i>is opening its doors again.</i>

73
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:01,313
<i>Preparations are nearly completed</i>
<i>for the United Nations World Summit.</i>

74
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:07,959
<i>The event promises to be the largest</i>
<i>single gathering of world leaders in history.</i>

75
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:13,279
<i>Leaders will discuss issues ranging from</i>
<i>the world's economy and weapons treaties,</i>

76
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:17,678
<i>to the mutant phenomenon</i>
<i>and its impact on our world stage.</i>

77
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:21,395
<i>American legislators contend</i>
<i>that debate over mutant issues</i>

78
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:26,719
<i>should be the primary focus of what is,</i>
<i>on the surface at least, a diplomatic affair.</i>

79
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:30,628
- You owe me some money.
- Stu, let's not do this.

80
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:34,435
No man takes a beating like that
without a mark to show for it.

81
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:37,791
- Come on, this isn't worth it.
- l know what you are.

82
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:42,675
You lost your money.
You keep this up, you lose something else.

83
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,236
Look out!

84
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,470
Get outta my bar, freak!

85
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:48,032
- What the hell are you doin'?
- l'm sorry. l needed a ride.

86
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:51,596
- l thought you might help me.
- Get out!

87
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,470
- Where am l supposed to go?
- l don't know.

88
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,717
- You don't know or you don't care?
- Pick one.

89
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,512
- l saved your life!
- No, you didn't.

90
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:21,077
You don't have anything to eat, do you?

91
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:43,676
l'm Rogue.

92
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:52,679
Were you in the army?
Doesn't that mean you were in the army?

93
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,434
- Wow!
- What?

94
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:07,832
- Suddenly <i>my</i> life isn't bad.
- lf you prefer the road...

95
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:11,236
No! lt looks great.

96
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,800
lt looks cosy.

97
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:26,197
Put your hands on the heater.

98
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:30,392
- l'm not gonna hurt you, kid.
- lt's nothing personal.

99
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:33,751
lt's just when people touch my skin,
something happens.

100
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:35,632
What?

101
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:38,320
l don't know. They just get hurt.

102
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:42,755
Fair enough.

103
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:48,518
When they come out, does it hurt?

104
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:53,995
Every time.

105
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,788
So what kind of a name is Rogue?

106
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:04,230
l don't know.
What kind of a name is Wolverine?

107
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:11,190
My name's Logan.

108
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,710
Marie.

109
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:20,713
- You should wear your seat belt.
- Look, kid, l don't need advice on...

110
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:26,508
You all right?

111
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,677
- Kid, are you all right?
- l'm stuck!

112
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:13,949
Weren't you supposed to bring
someone back with you?

113
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,076
- What happened?
- They knew.

114
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:38,398
Charles...

115
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:54,189
- Where is the mutant now?
- With them.

116
00:20:56,960 --> 00:21:01,078
l have made the first move.
That is all they know.

117
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:06,797
Come, the UN summit is approaching.
Time for our little test.

118
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:18,109
Where's he going?

119
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:44,800
Where are you going?

120
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,396
Over here!

121
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:20,988
- Where are you going?
- This way!

122
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:23,076
He's over there.

123
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:31,350
Let go! What's your hurry?

124
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:38,276
Over here!

125
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,189
Good morning, Logan.

126
00:23:57,320 --> 00:24:01,950
So, l'd like your definitions of weak and
strong anthropic principles on Wednesday.

127
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:04,036
That'll be all.

128
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:12,510
- Bye, Professor.
- Bye, Kitty.

129
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,836
Physics.

130
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:22,272
l'm Charles Xavier.
Would you like some breakfast?

131
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:24,994
- Where am l?
- Westchester, New York.

132
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:29,754
You were attacked. My people
brought you here for medical attention.

133
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:33,839
- l don't need medical attention.
- Yes, of course.

134
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:37,794
- Where's the girl?
- Rogue's here. She's fine.

135
00:24:37,920 --> 00:24:40,036
Really?

136
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:46,155
Ah. Logan, l'd like you to meet Ororo Monroe,
also called Storm.

137
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:49,238
This is Scott Summers, also called Cyclops.

138
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:54,515
They saved your life.

139
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:59,196
l believe you've already met Dr Jean Grey.

140
00:24:59,320 --> 00:25:04,235
You're in my school for the gifted. For
mutants. You'll be safe here from Magneto.

141
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:07,352
- What's a magneto?
- A very powerful mutant,

142
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:11,029
who believes a war is brewing
between mutants and the rest of humanity.

143
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,799
l've been following his activities
for some time.

144
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:17,356
The man who attacked you
is an associate of his called Sabretooth.

145
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,198
Sabretooth?

146
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:22,754
Storm.

147
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:26,433
What do they call you? Wheels?

148
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:31,310
This is the stupidest thing l've ever heard.

149
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:35,273
And Cyclops, right?

150
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,755
You wanna get outta my way?

151
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:41,997
Logan, it's been almost 15 years, hasn't it?

152
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:45,757
Living from day to day,
moving from place to place,

153
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:48,599
with no memory of who or what you are.

154
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,950
Shut up!

155
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:56,029
Give me a chance.
l may be able to help you find some answers.

156
00:25:57,400 --> 00:26:00,517
- How do you know?
- You're not the only one with gifts.

157
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:02,870
- Where are you going?
- Where's he going?

158
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,956
Over here!

159
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,753
What is this place?

160
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:17,117
Anonymity is a mutant's first defence
against the world's hostility.

161
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:19,196
Hey, no powers!

162
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:24,232
To the public, we're merely
a school for gifted youngsters.

163
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:28,069
Cyclops, Storm and Jean
were some of my first students.

164
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:31,875
l protected them,
taught them to control their powers

165
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,436
and, in time, teach others to do the same.

166
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:39,795
The students are mostly runaways -
frightened, alone.

167
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:44,675
Some with gifts so extreme they're a danger
to themselves and those around them.

168
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:46,438
Like your friend Rogue.

169
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:51,156
lncapable of physical human contact,
probably for the rest of her life.

170
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:56,195
And yet here she is with others her own age,
learning, being accepted,

171
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:58,276
not feared.

172
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:10,749
- John!
- Sorry.

173
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,875
l'm Bobby.

174
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,195
- What's your name?
- Rogue.

175
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:22,073
- What'll happen to her?
- That's up to her.

176
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:26,079
Rejoin the world as an educated
young woman, or stay on to teach others.

177
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:29,829
To become what the children
have affectionately called ''X-Men''.

178
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:32,235
Welcome to Mutant High.

179
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:37,238
But the school is merely our public face.

180
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:41,751
The lower levels, however,
are an entirely different matter.

181
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:49,557
When l was a boy l discovered l had
the power to control people's minds.

182
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:52,194
Make them think or do whatever l wanted.

183
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:56,233
When l was 17
l met a young man named Eric Lensherr.

184
00:27:56,360 --> 00:28:01,912
He, too, had an unusual power. He could
create magnetic fields and control metal.

185
00:28:02,040 --> 00:28:07,797
Believing that humanity would never
accept us, he grew angry and vengeful.

186
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,840
He became Magneto.

187
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:16,230
There are mutants out there
with incredible powers, Logan.

188
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:19,636
And many who do not share
my respect for mankind.

189
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:23,799
lf no one is equipped to oppose them,
humanity's days could be over.

190
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:25,990
l'll make a deal with you.

191
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:30,033
Give me 48 hours to find out
what Magneto wants with you,

192
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:32,913
and l give you my word
that l will use all my power

193
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:38,068
to help you piece together what you've lost,
and what you're looking for.

194
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:09,471
Senator, you favour gun registration, yes?
Some of these so-called children

195
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:14,310
possess more than 10 times
the destructive force of any handgun.

196
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:18,513
No, l don't see a difference.
All l see are weapons in our schools.

197
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,393
Well, that's fair enough. All right.

198
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:23,272
So?

199
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:26,836
lt's gonna be close.
A vote this loaded is always close.

200
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:29,997
What about the UN summit?
The world will be watching.

201
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:34,352
- Maybe you could use it to your advantage.
- We're Americans, Henry.

202
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:37,950
Let the rest of the damn world
deal with mutants in their own way.

203
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:41,117
You know this situation? These mutants?

204
00:29:42,320 --> 00:29:47,633
People like this Jean Grey?
lf it were up to me, l'd lock 'em all away.

205
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:51,270
lt's a war.

206
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:54,392
lt's the reason people like me exist.

207
00:30:01,440 --> 00:30:03,670
Where the hell are we?

208
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:15,077
Pilot!

209
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:22,316
People like you are the reason
l was afraid to go to school as a child.

210
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:54,276
l'm sorry.

211
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:58,073
- For what?
- lf l hurt you.

212
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:10,994
So... couldn't wait
to get my shirt off again, huh?

213
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:29,719
The metal is an alloy called adamantium.

214
00:31:29,840 --> 00:31:35,278
Supposedly indestructible. lt's been
surgically grafted to his entire skeleton.

215
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:38,472
How could he have survived
a procedure like that?

216
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:45,597
His mutation. He has uncharted regenerative
capability which enables him to heal rapidly.

217
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:48,996
This also makes his age
impossible to determine.

218
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:52,749
He could very well be older than you,
Professor.

219
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:55,599
- Who did this to him?
- He doesn't know.

220
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:58,996
Nor does he remember anything
about his life before it happened.

221
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:03,591
Experimentation on mutants.
lt's not unheard of.

222
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:07,238
But l've never seen anything like this before.

223
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,669
What do you think Magneto want with him?

224
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:13,349
l'm not entirely sure it's him Magneto wants.

225
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:39,792
Toad has a wicked tongue, Senator.

226
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:41,876
Just like you.

227
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:50,110
Who are you people? Where's Henry?

228
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:53,835
Mr Guyrich has been dead
for some time, Senator.

229
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:58,511
But l've had Mystique here keep you
company. She takes so many shapes.

230
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:01,837
Whatever you do to me, you'll make me right.

231
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:05,669
Every word l've spoken will be confirmed.

232
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:13,600
Are you a God-fearing man, Senator?
lt's such a strange phrase.

233
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:16,598
l've always thought of God as a teacher.

234
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:20,156
As a bringer of light,
wisdom and understanding.

235
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:24,273
You see,
l think what you really are afraid of is me.

236
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:28,518
Me and my kind.
The brotherhood of mutants.

237
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:37,589
lt's not so surprising, really. Mankind has
always feared what it doesn't understand.

238
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:44,194
Well, don't fear God, Senator,
and certainly don't fear me.

239
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,836
Not any more.

240
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:54,276
- What do you intend to do to me?
- Let's just say God works too slowly.

241
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:09,188
l think you'll be comfortable here.

242
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:13,074
- Where's your room?
- With Scott, down the hall.

243
00:35:14,120 --> 00:35:17,078
ls that your gift? Putting up with that guy?

244
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:20,749
Actually l'm telekinetic.
l can move things with my mind.

245
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,838
Really? What kinds of things?

246
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:26,597
All kinds of things.

247
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,758
- l also have telepathic ability.
- Like your professor?

248
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:35,715
Nowhere near that powerful.
But he's teaching me to develop it.

249
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,796
l'm sure he is.

250
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:41,556
- So read my mind.
- l'd rather not.

251
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:45,912
- Come on. You afraid you might like it?
- l doubt it.

252
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:09,474
What do you see?

253
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:11,397
Scott!

254
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:17,076
Good night, Logan.

255
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:27,350
You gonna tell me
to stay away from your girl?

256
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:30,358
lf l had to do that, she wouldn't be my girl.

257
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:34,473
Then l guess you've got nothing
to worry about, do you... Cyclops?

258
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:38,674
lt mustjust burn you up
that a boy like me saved your life, huh?

259
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:42,270
You oughta be careful.
l might not be there next time.

260
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:45,836
Oh, and Logan, stay away from my girl.

261
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:21,356
Logan?

262
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:32,752
Logan! Logan, wake up.

263
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,436
Help me!

264
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:12,233
Somebody, help!

265
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:43,836
Scott, grab a pillow.

266
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:48,634
lt was an accident.

267
00:38:57,800 --> 00:39:00,519
- Logan?
- What happened?

268
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:05,031
- ls she all right?
- She'll be all right.

269
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:09,397
- What did she do to me?
- When Rogue touches someone,

270
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:12,159
she takes their energy, their life force.

271
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:15,556
ln the case of mutants,
she absorbs their gifts for a while.

272
00:39:15,680 --> 00:39:18,114
ln your case, your ability to heal.

273
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:26,830
- lt felt like she almost killed me.
- lf she'd held out any longer, she could have.

274
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:22,036
How are we feeling, Senator?
Advanced, l hope.

275
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:40,995
What the hell have you done to me?

276
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:44,999
Senator, this is pointless.
Where would you go?

277
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:47,429
Who would take you in,
now you're one of us?

278
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:46,118
Tommy, let it go! Tommy, please let it go!

279
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:48,959
l'm telling Mommy.

280
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:04,400
ls that a mutant?

281
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:13,513
<i>..UN summit. With the leaders</i>
<i>of over 200 nations attending,</i>

282
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:17,918
<i>the Secret Service has transformed</i>
<i>Ellis lsland into a veritable Fort Knox</i>

283
00:42:18,040 --> 00:42:23,478
<i>for tomorrow night's opening gala.</i>
<i>Ellis lsland rests less than one mile from...</i>

284
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,997
Rogue!

285
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:29,111
Bobby!

286
00:42:29,240 --> 00:42:34,268
Rogue, what did you do? They say
you're stealing other mutants' powers.

287
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:36,356
No! l borrowed his power.

288
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:40,109
You never use your power
against another mutant.

289
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:43,116
l had no choice.

290
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:48,394
- No, you have to understand...
- lf l were you l'd get myself outta here.

291
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:54,113
- What do you mean?
- Listen, the students are freaked.

292
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:58,791
Professor Xavier's furious.
l don't know what he'll do with you.

293
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:03,753
l think it'll be easier on your own.

294
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:11,596
You should go.

295
00:43:33,040 --> 00:43:36,953
What are you looking for, Eric? lt's strange.

296
00:43:37,080 --> 00:43:41,790
There are more <i>powerful</i> mutants out there.
Why should this one be so important to him?

297
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:45,390
- Maybe it's his way with people.
- You don't like him.

298
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:48,990
- How could you tell?
- Well, l am psychic, you know.

299
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:52,198
- Where is she?
- Who?

300
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:54,595
Rogue.

301
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,119
She's gone.

302
00:44:00,440 --> 00:44:02,795
<i>Welcome, Professor.</i>

303
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:07,756
Welcome to Cerebro.

304
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:15,714
This certainly is a big, round room.

305
00:44:15,840 --> 00:44:19,071
The brain waves of mutants
are different from average humans.

306
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:24,194
This device amplifies my power, allowing me
to locate mutants across great distances.

307
00:44:24,320 --> 00:44:28,757
- That's how l intend to find Rogue.
- Why don't you just use it to find Magneto?

308
00:44:28,880 --> 00:44:33,271
l've been trying, but he's found
some way to shield himself from it.

309
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:36,392
How would he know how to do that?

310
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:38,829
Because he helped me build it.

311
00:44:38,960 --> 00:44:41,110
Now if you'll excuse me...

312
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:55,956
Have you ever...?

313
00:44:56,080 --> 00:44:58,036
Used Cerebro?

314
00:44:58,160 --> 00:45:00,151
No.

315
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:05,400
lt takes a degree of control and...
for someone like me, it's...

316
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:06,999
Dangerous.

317
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:46,030
<i>..now boarding at track 4.</i>

318
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:51,676
- She's at the station.
- Where is it?

319
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:57,113
A few miles west of here. You can't leave the
mansion. lt's the opportunity Magneto needs.

320
00:45:57,240 --> 00:46:00,789
- Listen, l'm the reason she took off.
- We had a deal.

321
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:03,593
She's all right. She's just upset.

322
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:07,998
Storm, Cyclops, find her.
See if you can talk to her.

323
00:46:16,040 --> 00:46:18,918
- What?
- Where's my motorcycle?

324
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,238
Hey, kid.

325
00:47:10,640 --> 00:47:12,995
l'm sorry about last night.

326
00:47:14,560 --> 00:47:16,516
Me, too.

327
00:47:17,320 --> 00:47:19,276
You running again?

328
00:47:20,760 --> 00:47:23,194
l heard the professor was mad at me.

329
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:26,596
- Who told you that?
- A boy at school.

330
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:31,794
- When's the last time you saw her?
- She was supposed to meet me for lunch.

331
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:39,029
You look around,
l'll check with the ticket agent.

332
00:47:51,520 --> 00:47:53,875
<i>Welcome, Professor.</i>

333
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:22,433
- You think l should go back.
- l think you should follow your instincts.

334
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:32,273
The first boy l ever kissed
ended up in a coma for three weeks.

335
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:37,400
l can still feel him inside my head.

336
00:48:38,800 --> 00:48:41,951
And it's the same with you.

337
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:11,674
There's not many people
that'll understand what you're going through.

338
00:49:11,800 --> 00:49:14,837
But l think this guy Xavier's one of them.

339
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:19,392
He seems to genuinely wanna help you.

340
00:49:19,520 --> 00:49:21,875
And that's a rare thing.

341
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:26,235
For people like us.

342
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:37,196
OK, so...

343
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:41,438
What do you say?
Give these geeks one more shot?

344
00:49:43,320 --> 00:49:45,675
Come on, l'll take care of you.

345
00:49:47,600 --> 00:49:50,160
- You promise?
- Yeah.

346
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:53,156
Yeah, l promise.

347
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:06,594
Come along now. l told you not to...

348
00:50:08,160 --> 00:50:11,550
She's about 17, my height,

349
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:14,877
has brown hair and she...

350
00:50:22,560 --> 00:50:25,279
Scream for me.

351
00:51:07,120 --> 00:51:09,839
Quit playing around.

352
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:51,790
You must be Wolverine.

353
00:51:53,520 --> 00:51:58,435
That remarkable metal doesn't run through
your entire body, does it?

354
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:09,992
Stop!

355
00:52:10,120 --> 00:52:11,872
Stop it!

356
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:16,957
- What the hell do you want with me?
- You? My dear boy!

357
00:52:17,080 --> 00:52:19,640
Whoever said l wanted <i>you</i>?

358
00:52:40,120 --> 00:52:41,439
Young people!

359
00:52:52,680 --> 00:52:55,274
<i>All right, hold it! Hold it right there.</i>

360
00:52:55,400 --> 00:52:59,678
<i>Stay where you are.</i>
<i>Put your hands over your heads. Now!</i>

361
00:53:29,320 --> 00:53:32,357
You Homo sapiens and your guns.

362
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:39,117
- That's enough, Eric.
- Let them go.

363
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:47,310
Why not come out where l can see you,
Charles?

364
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:52,395
What do you want her for?

365
00:53:52,520 --> 00:53:55,318
Can't you read my mind?

366
00:53:57,120 --> 00:53:59,475
What now? Save the girl?

367
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:04,279
You'll have to kill me, Charles.
And what will that accomplish?

368
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:09,190
Let them pass that law and they'll have you
in chains with a number on your forehead.

369
00:54:09,320 --> 00:54:12,835
- lt won't be that way.
- Then kill me and find out.

370
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:18,349
No? Then release me.

371
00:54:26,680 --> 00:54:28,910
Fine!

372
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:43,349
Care to press your luck, Charles?

373
00:54:47,240 --> 00:54:49,435
l don't think l can stop them all.

374
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:09,475
Still unwilling to make sacrifices.
That's what makes you weak.

375
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:23,234
Goodbye, Charles.

376
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:55,273
- You said he wanted <i>me.</i>
- l made a terrible mistake.

377
00:55:55,400 --> 00:56:00,110
His helmet was somehow designed
to block my telepathy.

378
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:03,516
Couldn't see what he was after
till it was too late.

379
00:56:03,640 --> 00:56:05,631
- Where are you going?
- To find her.

380
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:08,672
- How?
- The traditional way: look.

381
00:56:12,440 --> 00:56:15,512
- Logan, you can't do this alone.
- Who'll help me? You?

382
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:19,315
- So far, you've all done a bang-up job.
- Then help us. Fight <i>with</i> us.

383
00:56:19,440 --> 00:56:22,193
Fight with you? Join the team? Be an X-Man?

384
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:24,959
Who the hell do you think you are?
You're a mutant.

385
00:56:25,080 --> 00:56:27,799
The world is full of people
that hate and fear you

386
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:32,675
and you're wasting your time trying
to protect them. l got better things to do.

387
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:36,190
You know, Magneto's right.
There's a war coming.

388
00:56:36,320 --> 00:56:40,074
- Are you sure you're on the right side?
- At least l've chosen a side.

389
00:56:47,520 --> 00:56:49,909
l'm looking for Dr Jean Grey.

390
00:56:59,520 --> 00:57:01,476
Senator Kelly.

391
00:57:02,320 --> 00:57:04,880
l'm Professor Charles Xavier.

392
00:57:05,680 --> 00:57:09,719
l was afraid if l went to hospital,
they would...

393
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,796
Treat you like a mutant?

394
00:57:14,480 --> 00:57:17,552
We're not what you think. Not all of us.

395
00:57:18,120 --> 00:57:21,271
Tell it to the ones who did this to me.

396
00:57:25,480 --> 00:57:27,436
Senator...

397
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:34,315
l want you to try and relax.

398
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:40,675
l'm not going to hurt you.

399
00:58:30,080 --> 00:58:32,036
Welcome to the future.

400
00:58:33,360 --> 00:58:35,316
Brother.

401
00:58:40,840 --> 00:58:44,753
The machine emits radiation that triggers
mutation in ordinary human beings.

402
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:48,759
But the mutation is unnatural.
Kelly's body is rejecting it.

403
00:58:48,880 --> 00:58:53,112
- His cells began to break down immediately.
- What effect does it have on mutants?

404
00:58:53,240 --> 00:58:58,394
There appears to be none. But l fear
it will harm any normal person exposed to it.

405
00:58:58,520 --> 00:59:02,195
- So what does Magneto want with Rogue?
- l don't know.

406
00:59:05,320 --> 00:59:09,871
Wait a second. You said this machine
draws its power from Magneto.

407
00:59:10,000 --> 00:59:15,358
- And that it weakened him.
- Yes. ln fact, it nearly killed him.

408
00:59:16,240 --> 00:59:21,109
He's going to transfer his power to Rogue
and use her to power the machine.

409
00:59:24,120 --> 00:59:26,076
ls somebody there?

410
00:59:27,640 --> 00:59:30,279
Yes. l'm here.

411
00:59:32,240 --> 00:59:34,390
Please don't leave me!

412
00:59:37,120 --> 00:59:39,270
l don't want to be alone.

413
00:59:40,280 --> 00:59:42,236
All right.

414
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:53,554
Do you hate normal people?

415
00:59:55,520 --> 00:59:57,476
Sometimes.

416
00:59:58,320 --> 01:00:00,276
Why?

417
01:00:03,880 --> 01:00:05,836
l suppose...

418
01:00:06,960 --> 01:00:09,315
l'm afraid of them.

419
01:00:11,320 --> 01:00:13,470
Well...

420
01:00:13,600 --> 01:00:19,152
l think you've got one less person...
to be afraid of.

421
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:45,551
Cyclops, you and Storm ready the jet.
l'm gonna find Rogue. Get Logan a uniform.

422
01:00:45,680 --> 01:00:48,513
Wait a minute.
He's not coming with us, is he?

423
01:00:48,640 --> 01:00:52,110
- Yes.
- Sorry, but he'll endanger the mission and...

424
01:00:52,240 --> 01:00:55,152
l wasn't the one who gave the station
a new sunroof, pal.

425
01:00:55,280 --> 01:00:57,999
No, you were the one
who stabbed Rogue in the chest.

426
01:00:58,120 --> 01:01:01,112
Why don't you take your little mission
and stick it up...

427
01:01:01,240 --> 01:01:03,595
Senator Kelly is dead.

428
01:01:05,320 --> 01:01:07,311
l'm going to find her.

429
01:01:10,160 --> 01:01:11,115
Settle this.

430
01:01:47,320 --> 01:01:49,276
l'm sorry.

431
01:02:11,840 --> 01:02:15,435
You can still hear me... can't you?

432
01:02:23,520 --> 01:02:27,638
You've taught me everything in my life
that was ever worth knowing.

433
01:02:27,760 --> 01:02:30,115
And if anything happens...

434
01:02:32,640 --> 01:02:34,232
l'll take care of them.

435
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:49,033
Jean?

436
01:02:52,400 --> 01:02:54,550
Jean!

437
01:02:54,680 --> 01:02:56,875
No!

438
01:03:09,120 --> 01:03:10,838
Jean?

439
01:03:10,960 --> 01:03:12,916
Jean.

440
01:03:13,040 --> 01:03:14,996
Answer me. Please.

441
01:03:16,320 --> 01:03:18,390
l know where Magneto's going.

442
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:36,991
Magnificent, isn't she?

443
01:04:38,120 --> 01:04:41,829
- l've seen it.
- l first saw her in 1949.

444
01:04:43,080 --> 01:04:48,074
America was going to be
the land of tolerance. Of peace.

445
01:04:52,920 --> 01:04:55,275
Are you going to kill me?

446
01:04:59,640 --> 01:05:01,358
Yes.

447
01:05:01,480 --> 01:05:05,268
- Why?
- Because there is no land of tolerance.

448
01:05:05,400 --> 01:05:09,154
There is no peace, not here or anywhere else.

449
01:05:10,480 --> 01:05:15,634
Whole families destroyed simply because
they were born different from those in power.

450
01:05:15,760 --> 01:05:20,675
Well, after tonight,
the world's powerful will be just like us.

451
01:05:20,800 --> 01:05:23,394
They will return home as brothers.

452
01:05:23,880 --> 01:05:25,836
As mutants.

453
01:05:25,960 --> 01:05:28,315
Our cause will be theirs.

454
01:05:29,320 --> 01:05:32,357
Your sacrifice will mean our survival.

455
01:05:35,960 --> 01:05:39,873
l'll understand
if that comes as small consolation.

456
01:05:42,680 --> 01:05:44,636
Put her in the machine.

457
01:05:46,320 --> 01:05:48,276
l'll raise it.

458
01:05:49,440 --> 01:05:51,908
Magneto is here - Liberty lsland.

459
01:05:52,040 --> 01:05:57,717
Presumably his objective is to mutate the
world leaders at the summit on Ellis lsland.

460
01:05:57,840 --> 01:06:01,879
He doesn't know his machine kills,
and judging from what the professor saw

461
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:07,518
if Magneto gave Rogue enough power,
he could wipe out everyone in New York City.

462
01:06:07,640 --> 01:06:11,155
All right. We can insert here
at the George Washington Bridge.

463
01:06:11,280 --> 01:06:16,195
Come around the bank, just off of Manhattan,
land on the far side of Liberty lsland. Here.

464
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:18,390
What about harbour patrol? Radar?

465
01:06:18,520 --> 01:06:22,229
lf they have anything that can pick up <i>our</i>jet,
they deserve to catch us.

466
01:06:36,160 --> 01:06:38,993
You actually go outside in these things?

467
01:06:39,120 --> 01:06:42,635
What would you prefer? Yellow spandex?

468
01:06:49,360 --> 01:06:50,315
Whoa.

469
01:07:30,320 --> 01:07:33,198
There's the bridge. l'm takin' her down.

470
01:07:39,840 --> 01:07:41,796
Storm, some cover, please.

471
01:07:59,720 --> 01:08:03,554
Toad, Mystique, stay sharp. We're not alone.

472
01:08:03,680 --> 01:08:08,674
And you stay here. Once l've given my power
to the girl, l'll be temporarily weakened.

473
01:08:08,800 --> 01:08:11,155
You'll be my only defence.

474
01:08:18,160 --> 01:08:19,912
Sounds like a storm's comin'.

475
01:08:34,360 --> 01:08:37,079
- Sorry.
- You call that a landing?

476
01:08:49,240 --> 01:08:51,515
The torch.

