01:08:57,920 --> 01:09:02,914
<i>..the proceedings. The first dignitaries</i>
<i>started to arrive about an hour ago,</i>

478
01:09:03,040 --> 01:09:06,828
<i>greeted with a garden-party atmosphere</i>
<i>designed to entertain them</i>

479
01:09:06,960 --> 01:09:09,349
<i>as the others traversed the rigid security.</i>

480
01:09:33,920 --> 01:09:36,480
- There's someone here.
- Where?

481
01:09:37,400 --> 01:09:40,278
- l don't know. Keep your eye open.
- Logan...

482
01:09:43,680 --> 01:09:45,591
Damn it!

483
01:09:51,320 --> 01:09:55,313
- Anything?
- There's someone here. l just can't see 'em.

484
01:10:07,640 --> 01:10:08,959
Wait!

485
01:10:15,720 --> 01:10:17,836
Back up! Back up!

486
01:11:31,480 --> 01:11:32,913
Jean!

487
01:11:34,360 --> 01:11:35,588
Oh, God!

488
01:12:33,040 --> 01:12:35,156
Don't move.

489
01:12:51,120 --> 01:12:53,714
Don't you people ever die?

490
01:13:25,320 --> 01:13:29,791
Do you know what happens to a toad
when it's struck by lightning?

491
01:13:35,160 --> 01:13:38,436
The same thing
that happens to everything else.

492
01:13:52,360 --> 01:13:54,715
Logan, is that you?

493
01:14:05,600 --> 01:14:08,512
The other one ain't far away.

494
01:14:08,640 --> 01:14:12,838
- Come on. We have to regroup.
- l know, but there's a problem.

495
01:14:15,960 --> 01:14:18,349
You're not part of the group.

496
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:40,629
Hey, hey! lt's me.

497
01:14:40,760 --> 01:14:43,115
- Prove it.
- You're a dick.

498
01:14:44,320 --> 01:14:46,117
OK.

499
01:14:47,400 --> 01:14:48,753
Hey!

500
01:15:07,320 --> 01:15:10,312
- Everybody get out of here.
- What is it?

501
01:15:10,440 --> 01:15:12,396
l can't move.

502
01:15:31,320 --> 01:15:33,470
Ah, my brothers.

503
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:39,911
Welcome. And you, just point those claws
of yours in a safer direction.

504
01:15:53,200 --> 01:15:55,350
You better close your eyes.

505
01:15:58,360 --> 01:16:00,157
Storm, fry 'em.

506
01:16:00,280 --> 01:16:07,277
A bolt of lightning into a huge copper
conductor. l thought you lived at a school.

507
01:16:12,320 --> 01:16:16,233
For those of you not familiar
with the historical significance...

508
01:16:20,640 --> 01:16:22,596
Mystique?

509
01:16:23,360 --> 01:16:27,035
- Mystique!
- l've seen Senator Kelly.

510
01:16:27,640 --> 01:16:32,998
So, the good senator survived his fall.
And the swim to shore.

511
01:16:33,120 --> 01:16:35,588
He's become even more powerful
than l imagined.

512
01:16:35,720 --> 01:16:38,234
- He's dead.
- lt's true.

513
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:42,319
l saw him die.
Like those people down there will die.

514
01:16:43,080 --> 01:16:45,833
Are you sure you saw what you saw?

515
01:16:45,960 --> 01:16:50,078
l would also like to thank the
President of the United States of America

516
01:16:50,200 --> 01:16:55,672
for hosting this event under the lights
of the great city of New York.

517
01:17:02,760 --> 01:17:06,548
Why do none of you understand
what l'm trying to do?

518
01:17:06,680 --> 01:17:11,959
Those people down there control our fate
and the fate of every other mutant!

519
01:17:13,320 --> 01:17:15,436
Well...

520
01:17:15,560 --> 01:17:18,028
soon our fate will be theirs.

521
01:17:18,160 --> 01:17:21,277
<i>Help! Please help me!</i>

522
01:17:22,040 --> 01:17:27,319
You're so full of shit. lf you're really
so righteous, it'd be <i>you</i> in that thing.

523
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:32,756
Help! Somebody help me!

524
01:17:45,120 --> 01:17:47,076
<i>Please!</i>

525
01:17:48,680 --> 01:17:50,591
<i>Somebody please help me!</i>

526
01:17:55,960 --> 01:17:59,236
Somebody! Help me...

527
01:18:10,000 --> 01:18:12,230
Logan!

528
01:19:05,360 --> 01:19:08,591
- l'm sorry, my dear.
- Don't do this.

529
01:19:20,520 --> 01:19:22,476
This is mine.

530
01:20:22,840 --> 01:20:24,876
You owe me a scream.

531
01:20:28,320 --> 01:20:31,915
Hey, bub, l'm not finished with you yet.

532
01:20:35,440 --> 01:20:38,034
- Jean.
- Scott, when l tell you, open your eyes.

533
01:20:38,160 --> 01:20:39,115
- No!
- Trust me.

534
01:20:39,240 --> 01:20:41,708
You drop something?

535
01:20:45,480 --> 01:20:47,436
Now!

536
01:21:01,000 --> 01:21:02,991
- Thanks.
- Don't mention it.

537
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:07,992
- Gotta get her outta there. Can you hit it?
- The rings are moving too fast.

538
01:21:08,120 --> 01:21:10,793
- Shoot it!
- l'll kill her! Storm, can you get me up?

539
01:21:10,920 --> 01:21:14,037
- l can't control it like that.
- Then let me go.

540
01:21:15,640 --> 01:21:20,509
lf l don't make it,
at least you can still blast the damn thing.

541
01:21:21,320 --> 01:21:25,199
All right, do it!
Jean, use your power. Try to steady him.

542
01:21:26,760 --> 01:21:28,716
Hang on to something.

543
01:22:21,000 --> 01:22:23,560
Scott, wait!

544
01:22:51,680 --> 01:22:53,955
- Jean, l have to!
- Just wait!

545
01:22:55,760 --> 01:22:58,194
l have a shot.

546
01:22:58,320 --> 01:23:00,117
l'm taking it.

547
01:23:38,720 --> 01:23:41,075
Come on...

548
01:25:07,720 --> 01:25:11,269
Hey, this one's alive. Let's get him outta here.

549
01:25:36,160 --> 01:25:40,039
Welcome back. l knew you'd find your way.

550
01:25:40,160 --> 01:25:42,116
l had you to guide me.

551
01:25:45,120 --> 01:25:47,475
How did we do?

552
01:26:13,840 --> 01:26:16,434
Oh, that tickles.

553
01:26:16,560 --> 01:26:18,516
Hey.

554
01:26:19,720 --> 01:26:21,312
Hey.

555
01:26:21,440 --> 01:26:23,396
How are you feeling?

556
01:26:23,520 --> 01:26:25,476
Fantastic.

557
01:26:26,680 --> 01:26:29,148
That was a brave thing you did.

558
01:26:30,440 --> 01:26:33,000
- Did it work?
- Yeah.

559
01:26:33,120 --> 01:26:39,673
She's fine. She took on a few of your
more charming personality traits for a while.

560
01:26:40,560 --> 01:26:42,915
But we lived through it.

561
01:26:45,400 --> 01:26:47,914
l think she's a little taken with you.

562
01:26:48,040 --> 01:26:52,352
Well, you can tell her
my heart belongs to someone else.

563
01:26:56,960 --> 01:26:59,110
You know, you and l...

564
01:26:59,240 --> 01:27:01,196
How's the professor?

565
01:27:03,040 --> 01:27:05,190
He's good.

566
01:27:05,320 --> 01:27:07,276
Good.

567
01:27:11,760 --> 01:27:15,958
There's an abandoned military compound
at Alkali Lake in the Canadian Rockies

568
01:27:16,080 --> 01:27:20,039
close to where we found you.
There's not much left but...

569
01:27:20,160 --> 01:27:22,515
you might find some answers.

570
01:27:24,600 --> 01:27:28,434
- Thank you.
- Are you going to say goodbye to them?

571
01:27:30,880 --> 01:27:33,917
<i>The Mutant Registration Act</i>
<i>lost its main proponent</i>

572
01:27:34,040 --> 01:27:36,713
<i>with the reversal of Senator Robert Kelly</i>

573
01:27:36,840 --> 01:27:41,118
<i>who until now had provided the loudest</i>
<i>voice in the cry for mutant registration.</i>

574
01:27:41,240 --> 01:27:46,917
<i>l was wrong in this particular issue and l</i>
<i>hope, in time, l may be forgiven. Thank you.</i>

575
01:27:47,040 --> 01:27:49,952
<i>The Mutant Registration Act</i>
<i>continues to draw support...</i>

576
01:27:50,080 --> 01:27:52,036
Mystique.

577
01:27:53,080 --> 01:27:55,036
Son of a bitch.

578
01:27:57,040 --> 01:28:02,319
<i>..from many parents'rights groups</i>
<i>who feel threatened by unidentified mutants.</i>

579
01:28:02,440 --> 01:28:08,709
<i>ln a related story, the body of Senator Kelly's</i>
<i>aide, Henry Guyrich, was found today.</i>

580
01:28:08,840 --> 01:28:13,994
<i>Preliminary coroner's reports seem to</i>
<i>indicate that Guyrich was mauled by a bear.</i>

581
01:28:14,440 --> 01:28:16,396
Hey!

582
01:28:20,400 --> 01:28:23,358
- You running again?
- Not really.

583
01:28:24,800 --> 01:28:27,951
l have some things to take care of up north.

584
01:28:33,120 --> 01:28:35,270
l kinda like it.

585
01:28:39,120 --> 01:28:41,475
l don't want you to go.

586
01:28:54,240 --> 01:28:56,595
l'll be back for this.

587
01:29:33,120 --> 01:29:35,395
Doesn't it ever wake you in the night,

588
01:29:35,520 --> 01:29:40,310
the feeling that someday they will pass
that foolish law, or one just like it,

589
01:29:40,440 --> 01:29:42,476
and come for you?

590
01:29:42,600 --> 01:29:44,750
And your children?

591
01:29:48,000 --> 01:29:50,355
lt does indeed.

592
01:29:54,760 --> 01:29:57,593
What do you do when you wake up to that?

593
01:29:57,720 --> 01:30:04,319
l feel a swell of pity for the poor soul who
comes to that school looking for trouble.

594
01:30:12,600 --> 01:30:14,556
Why do you come here, Charles?

595
01:30:14,680 --> 01:30:18,036
Why do you ask questions
to which you already know the answers?

596
01:30:18,160 --> 01:30:22,312
Oh, yes. Your continuing search for hope.

597
01:30:32,520 --> 01:30:36,195
You know this plastic prison of theirs
won't hold me for ever.

598
01:30:36,320 --> 01:30:40,757
The war is still coming, Charles,
and l intend to fight it.

599
01:30:41,720 --> 01:30:44,280
By any means necessary.

600
01:30:45,080 --> 01:30:47,435
And l will always be there.

601
01:30:49,000 --> 01:30:51,355
Old friend.

